    benefit: `Monthly benefit amounts vary by living arrangement, income, and county of residence. For 2026, the federal benefit for an individual is $994 and for a couple is $1,491. State supplements are added to these amounts. Examples: Living Alone: Individual combined benefit $1,081 ($994 Federal + $87 State); Couple combined benefit $1,595 ($1,491 Federal + $104 State). Living with Others: Individual combined benefit $1,017 ($662.67 Federal + $23 State); Couple combined benefit $1,040 ($994 Federal + $46 State). Congregate Care Level 1 - Family Care (NYC, Nassau, Rockland, Suffolk, Westchester Counties): Individual combined benefit $1,260.48 ($994 Federal + $266.48 State); Couple combined benefit $2,520.96 ($1,491 Federal + $1,029.96 State). Congregate Care Level 1 - Family Care (Rest of State): Individual combined benefit $1,222.48 ($994 Federal + $228.48 State); Couple combined benefit $2,444.96 ($1,491 Federal + $953.96 State). Congregate Care Level 2 - Residential Care (NYC, Nassau, Rockland, Suffolk, Westchester Counties): Individual combined benefit $1,429 ($994 Federal + $435 State); Couple combined benefit $2,858 ($1,491 Federal + $1,367 State). Congregate Care Level 2 - Residential Care (Rest of State): Individual combined benefit $1,399 ($994 Federal + $405 State); Couple combined benefit $2,798 ($1,491 Federal + $1,307 State). Congregate Care Level 3 - Enhanced Residential Care: Individual combined benefit $1,688 ($994 Federal + $694 State); Couple combined benefit $3,376 ($1,491 Federal + $1,885 State).`,
